properties.areaDesc: East Slopes of the Washington Cascades
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 4 at 8:50AM PST until February 5 at 7:00AM PST by NWS Pendleton OR
properties.description:
...WINTER STORM TO IMPACT THE REGION THROUGH WEDNESDAY EVENING...

.A storm system will move into the region this afternoon.
Abundant moisture will result in heavy amounts of snow for the
mountains and high valleys before snow levels rise and
precipitation changes to rain overnight and Wednesday.

* WHAT...Snow expected for Western Kittitas County. Total snow
accumulations of 4 to 8 inches. Winds gusting as high as 40
mph.

* WHERE...East Slopes of the Washington Cascades.

* WHEN...From 4 PM this afternoon to 7 AM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 7 AM PST WEDNESDAY FOR WESTERN KITTITAS COUNTY
